---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="TinyGoat - AI Adoption for Revenue Teams" description="We help sales leaders, RevOps teams, and founders get confident with AI and turn scattered experiments into workflows that actually save time.">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Subtle Atmospheric Background -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden pointer-events-none">
      <div class="absolute -top-1/4 -right-1/4 w-[800px] h-[800px] bg-teal/5 rounded-full blur-[150px]"></div>
      <div class="absolute -bottom-1/4 -left-1/4 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-gold/5 rounded-full blur-[120px]"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Noise Texture Overlay -->
    <div class="fixed inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-[0.03] mix-blend-multiply" style="background-image: url('/noise.png'); background-repeat: repeat;"></div>

    <!-- Content Layer -->
    <div class="relative z-10">
      <!-- Navigation -->
      <nav class="py-6 px-6 md:px-12 flex items-center justify-between max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center">
          <img src="/tinygoat-logo.png" alt="TinyGoat" class="h-20 md:h-24 w-auto" width="96" height="96" />
        </a>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-6">
          <a href="#services" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-navy transition-colors text-sm font-medium hidden md:block">Services</a>
          <a href="#about" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-navy transition-colors text-sm font-medium hidden md:block">About</a>
          <a href="#faq" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-navy transition-colors text-sm font-medium hidden md:block">FAQ</a>
          <button onclick="Calendly.initPopupWidget({url: 'https://calendly.com/gabby-tinygoat/30min'});return false;" class="inline-flex items-center px-5 py-2.5 bg-gold text-navy font-semibold text-sm rounded-full hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-gold/25 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 cursor-pointer">
            Chat with Us
          </button>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section class="px-6 md:px-12 py-20 md:py-32 max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-navy text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-extrabold leading-[1.05] mb-8">
          AI won't fix your revenue workflow. Adoption will.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg md:text-xl mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          We help sales leaders, RevOps teams, and founders get confident with AI and turn scattered experiments into workflows that actually save time.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <button
            onclick="Calendly.initPopupWidget({url: 'https://calendly.com/gabby-tinygoat/30min'});return false;"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-gold text-navy font-semibold text-lg rounded-full hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-gold/25 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 cursor-pointer"
          >
            Book a Discovery Call
          </button>
          <a
            href="#how-we-work"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 border-2 border-navy text-navy font-semibold text-lg rounded-full hover:bg-navy hover:text-white transition-all duration-300"
          >
            See How We Work
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Problems We Solve Section -->
      <section id="problems" class="px-6 md:px-12 py-24 md:py-32 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-navy text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-6">
            Sound familiar?
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-center text-lg mb-16 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Leadership says "adopt AI." Your team nods, opens ChatGPT twice, and goes back to doing everything manually.
          </p>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-10 mb-12">
            <!-- Problem Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-3">The mandate without the map</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                The board or exec team wants AI in every workflow. But nobody's defined which workflows, which tools, or what "adoption" even looks like. So the team stalls.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Problem Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-3">Tool overload</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Your team has been handed 4 different AI tools in the last 6 months. Nobody uses any of them consistently. The stack grows. The manual work stays the same.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Problem Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-3">Experimentation without adoption</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                A few reps tried using AI for outreach or research. Some of it worked. None of it became a repeatable process. There's no system, just scattered experiments.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Problem Card 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-3">The productivity gap</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Your team still spends 30–40% of their day on prospect research, CRM updates, pipeline hygiene, and reporting. AI could cut that in half. It hasn't, because nobody's built the workflows.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-navy text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-8">
            These aren't AI problems. They're adoption problems. That's what we solve.
          </p>

          <div class="text-center">
            <button
              onclick="Calendly.initPopupWidget({url: 'https://calendly.com/gabby-tinygoat/30min'});return false;"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-gold text-navy font-semibold rounded-full hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-gold/25 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 cursor-pointer"
            >
              Sound like your team? Let's talk.
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Who This Is For Section -->
      <section class="px-6 md:px-12 py-12 md:py-16">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <h2 class="text-navy text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">
            Who this is for.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Revenue teams that have been told to "use AI" or know they should be, but haven't been shown how.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2 md:gap-3">
            <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-full text-navy text-sm font-medium shadow-sm">VP Sales</span>
            <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-full text-navy text-sm font-medium shadow-sm">CRO</span>
            <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-full text-navy text-sm font-medium shadow-sm">Sales Managers</span>
            <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-full text-navy text-sm font-medium shadow-sm">Player-Coach</span>
            <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-full text-navy text-sm font-medium shadow-sm">RevOps</span>
            <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-full text-navy text-sm font-medium shadow-sm">Sales Enablement</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- The TinyGoat Difference Section -->
      <section class="px-6 md:px-12 py-24 md:py-32 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-navy text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-6">
            The TinyGoat difference.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-teal text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-6">
            AI training for sales teams — taught by someone who's actually carried a quota.
          </p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 items-center">
            <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-6 text-lg md:pr-0 md:-mr-6 md:-mt-6">
              <p>
                Most AI consultants come from engineering or marketing. They understand the tools, but they haven't run a pipeline or closed complex deals.
              </p>
              <p>
                Before TinyGoat, I spent years as a top-performing AE working with organizations of all sizes. That experience shapes how I approach AI today: practical workflows that actually help sellers save time and move deals forward.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center md:mt-4">
              <img src="/Meandsanti.jpeg" alt="Gabby and Santiago" class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg mx-auto max-h-[24rem]" loading="lazy" />
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-4 italic">with the TinyGoat himself, Santiago</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Services Section -->
      <section id="services" class="px-6 md:px-12 py-24 md:py-32">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-navy text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-16">
            Three ways we work with revenue teams.
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-12">
            <!-- Service 1: AI Assessment -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-teal/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-teal" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-6 9l2 2 4-4" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-navy text-2xl font-bold">AI Assessment</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-teal font-semibold mb-4">Find out where AI actually moves the needle.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                We evaluate your current revenue workflows (prospecting, outreach, CRM, pipeline management, reporting) and identify where AI can realistically reduce manual work and improve efficiency. No vendor pitches. No theoretical frameworks. Just a clear-eyed assessment of what's worth building.
              </p>
              <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-3">You walk away with:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">An AI opportunity map for your revenue workflow</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Tool and process recommendations tailored to your stack</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">A prioritized implementation roadmap your team can actually execute</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm italic">Best for: Sales leaders or RevOps teams who know they should be using AI but aren't sure where to start.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Service 2: AI Training -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gold" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-navy text-2xl font-bold">AI Training</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gold font-semibold mb-4">Get your team confident, not just curious.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Hands-on workshops and training sessions that teach your revenue team how to use AI tools in their actual daily work. Not in theory, not in a demo environment. We cover prompting, prospecting workflows, research automation, and communication, calibrated to what your team actually does.
              </p>
              <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-3">Formats include:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Team workshops (virtual or onsite)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Sales kickoff or offsite sessions</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Ongoing enablement for managers and reps</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm italic">Best for: Sales teams and managers who've been told to "use AI" but haven't been shown how.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Service 3: AI Implementation -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-navy/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-navy" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M10.325 4.317c.426-1.756 2.924-1.756 3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 002.573 1.066c1.543-.94 3.31.826 2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 001.065 2.572c1.756.426 1.756 2.924 0 3.35a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066 2.573c.94 1.543-.826 3.31-2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.572 1.065c-.426 1.756-2.924 1.756-3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573-1.066c-1.543.94-3.31-.826-2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.065-2.572c-1.756-.426-1.756-2.924 0-3.35a1.724 1.724 0 001.066-2.573c-.94-1.543.826-3.31 2.37-2.37.996.608 2.296.07 2.572-1.065z" />
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-navy text-2xl font-bold">AI Implementation</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-4">Build the systems your team will actually use.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                We design and implement practical AI workflows that plug into your existing revenue operations. This isn't a science project. Every system we build is designed to reduce manual work and be usable by real salespeople on day one.
              </p>
              <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-3">Examples:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">AI-assisted prospect research workflows</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">CRM automation and pipeline hygiene</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Internal sales enablement systems</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Outbound and communication workflows</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm italic">Best for: Teams ready to move beyond experimentation and operationalize AI across the revenue process.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center mt-12">
            <button
              onclick="Calendly.initPopupWidget({url: 'https://calendly.com/gabby-tinygoat/30min'});return false;"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-gold text-navy font-semibold rounded-full hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-gold/25 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 cursor-pointer"
            >
              Not sure which service fits? Start with a discovery call.
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- How We Work Section -->
      <section id="how-we-work" class="px-6 md:px-12 py-24 md:py-32 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-navy text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-16">
            How we work.
          </h2>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
            <!-- Step 1 -->
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-teal/10 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
                <span class="text-teal text-2xl font-bold">1</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-4">Assess</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                We start by understanding your current revenue workflows, your team's tools, and where the manual bottlenecks are. No assumptions. No prescriptions until we've seen the real picture.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 2 -->
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
                <span class="text-gold text-2xl font-bold">2</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-4">Train</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                We get your team up to speed on the AI tools and workflows that are relevant to their work. Not a generic "intro to AI" session. Practical, role-specific, and immediately applicable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 3 -->
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-navy/10 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
                <span class="text-navy text-2xl font-bold">3</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-navy text-xl font-bold mb-4">Implement</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                We build the workflows, automations, and systems that make AI part of how your team actually operates, not just something they tried once in a workshop.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-600 text-center text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Every engagement is scoped to your team. Some clients need all three. Some need one. We figure that out together on the discovery call.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- About Section -->
      <section id="about" class="px-6 md:px-12 py-24 md:py-32">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
            <div>
              <!-- Headshot -->
              <div class="w-32 h-32 md:w-40 md:h-40 rounded-full overflow-hidden mb-6 border-4 border-white shadow-xl">
                <img src="/Website Photo.png" alt="Gabrielle Schiavenato" class="w-full h-full object-cover object-[50%_35%] scale-150" width="160" height="160" loading="lazy" />
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-navy text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">
                Built by someone who's carried a quota.
              </h2>
              <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
                <p>
                  Most AI consultants come from engineering or operations. They understand the technology. They don't understand sales organizations.
                </p>
                <p>
                  I'm Gabby. I spent years as a top-performing AE selling B2B, closing deals with startups, agencies, and billion-dollar multinationals. I've run complex full sales cycles from cold outreach to account management, built sales processes from scratch, and worked inside the exact kind of revenue teams I now consult for.
                </p>
                <p>
                  That background is the reason TinyGoat exists. When I started helping companies adopt AI, I kept seeing the same pattern: smart tools built by people who'd never sat across from a buyer, implemented by people who'd never managed a pipeline. The technology was fine. The adoption failed because nobody understood how salespeople actually work.
                </p>
                <p>
                  TinyGoat bridges that gap. I know which workflows actually eat your team's time. I know which AI tools reps will actually use versus which ones become shelfware. And I know the difference between a system that looks impressive in a demo and one that survives first contact with a real sales week.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                <p class="text-navy font-bold text-lg">Gabby Schiavenato</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Founder, TinyGoat</p>
                <p class="text-gray-500 italic mt-2">AI training for sales teams — taught by someone who's actually carried a quota.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <!-- Proof Point Badges -->
              <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-100 shadow-sm">
                <div class="space-y-5">
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                    <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-teal/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                      <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                      </svg>
